### 2.2 Autor Original ✅

**Funciona correctamente.**

```
UI (ScaleBuilder)           -> Schema (config.original_author)
Schema                      -> publishScale -> INSERT/UPDATE medical_scales.original_author
BD (medical_scales)         -> getScaleById -> config.original_author ✅
```

---

### 2.3 Información de Validación ✅

**Estado: CORREGIDO**

[publishScale](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#311-569) ahora envía `evidence_level: scaleData.current_version?.config.validation_info` en insert y update.
[getScaleById](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#207-295) carga `validation_info: data.evidence_level`.

```typescript
// ScaleService.ts — publishScale INSERT/UPDATE (corregido)
{
    name, acronym, description, category, tags, status,
    instructions, time_to_complete, language, original_author,
    evidence_level: scaleData.current_version?.config.validation_info // ✅
}
```

---

### 2.4 Idioma ✅

**Funciona correctamente.**

- Guardado: [publishScale()](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#311-569) -> `language: scaleData.current_version?.config.language`
- Carga: [getScaleById()](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#207-295) -> `language: data.language`

---

### 2.5 Referencias Bibliográficas ✅

**Funciona correctamente.**

```
UI (bibliography[])  -> publishScale PASO 4 -> DELETE + INSERT scale_references
BD (scale_references) -> getScaleById -> config.bibliography
```

Tabla `scale_references` con columnas: `scale_id`, `title`, `authors` (text[]), `year`, `journal`, `doi`, `pmid`, `url`, `reference_type`, `is_primary`.

---

## 3. Carga al Editar (Corregido)

Cuando se **edita una escala existente**, todos los campos se cargan correctamente:

| Campo | ¿Se carga al editar? | Detalle |
|-------|---------------------|---------|
| `original_author` | ✅ Sí | [getScaleById](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#207-295) -> `config.original_author: data.original_author` |
| `validation_info` / `evidence_level` | ✅ Sí | [getScaleById](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#207-295) -> `config.validation_info: data.evidence_level` |
| `language` | ✅ Sí | [getScaleById](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#207-295) -> `config.language: data.language` |
| Taxonomy IDs | ✅ Sí | [ScaleBuilder](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/components/ScaleBuilder.tsx#52-1382) carga via `useEffect` -> `TaxonomyService.getScaleTaxonomies()` |

---

## 4. Importador JSON

El [JSONImporter.tsx](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/components/JSONImporter.tsx) llama directamente a `ScaleService.publishScale(scaleToImport)`, por lo tanto:

- ✅ Guarda todo lo que [publishScale](file:///c:/Users/JmYoc/OneDrive/Documentos/DeepLuxMed/Escalas/Nuevas%20Escalas/services/ScaleService.ts#311-569) soporta (name, acronym, scoring, questions, references, language, original_author, evidence_level)
- ⚠️ Taxonomy no se guarda desde el importador JSON (no tiene UI de selección de taxonomía)
- Las taxonomías se asignan desde la UI del Constructor al editar la escala importada

---

## 5. Mapa de Tablas en Supabase

```mermaid
erDiagram
    medical_scales {
        uuid id PK
        text name
        text acronym
        text description
        text category
        text[] tags
        text status
        text original_author
        text evidence_level
        text language
        text instructions
        text time_to_complete
        uuid created_by FK
    }

    scale_references {
        uuid id PK
        uuid scale_id FK
        text title
        text[] authors
        int year
        text journal
        text doi
        text pmid
        text url
        text reference_type
        bool is_primary
    }

    medical_categories {
        uuid id PK
        text name_es
        text name_en
        text icon
        text color
    }

    scale_medical_categories {
        uuid scale_id FK
        uuid category_id FK
    }

    medical_specialties {
        uuid id PK
        text name_es
        text name_en
    }

    scale_specialties {
        uuid scale_id FK
        uuid specialty_id FK
    }

    body_systems {
        uuid id PK
        text name_es
        text name_en
    }

    scale_body_systems {
        uuid scale_id FK
        uuid system_id FK
    }

    target_populations {
        uuid id PK
        text name_es
        text name_en
        text age_range
    }

    scale_populations {
        uuid scale_id FK
        uuid population_id FK
    }

    scale_types {
        uuid id PK
        text name_es
        text name_en
    }

    scale_scale_types {
        uuid scale_id FK
        uuid type_id FK
    }

    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_references : "has"
    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_medical_categories : "classified by"
    scale_medical_categories }o--|| medical_categories : "references"
    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_specialties : "belongs to"
    scale_specialties }o--|| medical_specialties : "references"
    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_body_systems : "targets"
    scale_body_systems }o--|| body_systems : "references"
    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_populations : "applies to"
    scale_populations }o--|| target_populations : "references"
    medical_scales ||--o{ scale_scale_types : "is type of"
    scale_scale_types }o--|| scale_types : "references"
```

